  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">219012_Zimbabwe EOL - Adolescent Mothers&apos; Education Initiative</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This is an advocacy in education project which is being implemented in 3 countries: DRC, Uganda and Zimbabwe (PIMS only allows me to input one country). The project is called Adolescent Mothers&apos; Education Initiative (AMEI) and is aimed at supporting the development of policies that support the continued education of pregnant girls and the re-entry of adolescent mothers back into school. WVUK is leading a consortium WV Zimbabwe, WV DRC, Education Coalition of Zimbabwe (ECOZI), CONEPT (DRC) and the Initiative for Social and Economic Rights (ISER). It is being funded by the Global Partnership for Education with Oxfam IBIS (Denmark) as the fund manager.</narrative>
  </description>
